            </div>
            <div id="projectpara">
                <h5>-	How long is the game?
                    The Game can be around 15-30 minutes long. Due to the limited skills I have learned I aimed to learn more and be more improvised, I believe an escape room with the puzzles being at the basic level with 3-4 levels will only around 15 minutes to 30 minutes. Each levels (rooms) consist of Multiple Puzzles where they need to be unlocked and solved in the right order to solve the next puzzle and clear the room. Some puzzles require hints where some hints are as simple as hidden away in the room while some may require mini puzzle solved to find the hint. Each Room may take around Several minutes, as difficulty gets harder for each puzzle, the time taken should increase. Estimate:
                     1st room- 7 mins
                    2nd room – 7-8 mins
                    3rd room – 8-10 mins
                    If every room takes the maximum estimated time, a player will fail to escape and be frozen in time(die) 
                    -	How many levels are there?
                    -	What is the average playtime?
                    Average play time should is around 15-30 minutes
                    -	What are the objectives?
                    The objectives of the game is for players to be flexible and think of all the possibilities the key or code could be hidden or crafted/formed to unlock the game and not be inflexible and overly Logical while feeling the thrill of racing against literal time itself to escape the room.
                    </h5>
            </div>
