            </div>
            <div id="projectpara">
                <h5>
                    A dedicated Gamer player may find this kind of Escape room game exciting on first try, being able to compete with other gamers on who being the fastest to escape it and boast about it which Is a big part of their personality trait. However, this may only last for one or two times for a dedicated gamer as playing the same Escape room game again will get repetitive and cause them to quickly lose interest.
A play to win gamer is actually one of the more targeted audience of my VR game as they tend to be not only competitive, but focused, which is one of the main factor to win this my escape room game. As they are focused, they will constantly be thinking about the puzzles and searching for the keys to escape as fast as possible. They are also determined, meaning they will likely not give up halfway in the game and will keep trying till they escape it, no matter how many tries it takes.
Participant Parents are an unique yet encouraged players to try out and play my escape room game with their kids or one another. As a parent playing and competing with their own children will mean my VR game get to serve as a form of entertainment for a whole family to spend time together. A parent can also brainstorm and teamwork together with their children to help each other escape the Escape Room together, which serves one of my game concepts of “Teamwork”.
A story seeker is another one of my targeted audiences for my VR escape room game. One of my main selling points of the game is based on its origin storyline that pique players interest and immerse themselves in the escape room and try to escape the lab before the malfunctioned time device stops time within the room. A story seeker will definitely be attracted to the VR game upon finding out that there is a story behind it. Story seekers enjoy reading and especially experiencing through the story themselves, therefore my VR game that consist of a storyline /lore behind the VR escape room process will be sure to attract many story seekers compare to other players types.

                </h5>
